messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
- The user wants an automation triggered by a physical turn on of Kitchen Counter 1.
- Physical turn on corresponds to a COC event with command "DFON" from Kitchen Counter 1.
- When this occurs, the action is to set brightness to 200 (unit Level) and color temperature to 3000K.
- The transition time should be 5000 milliseconds (5 seconds).
- The device supports the command "Set Temp and Brightness [SET_CTBR]" which accepts parameters: Color Temperature (Kelvin), Transition Time (ms), and Brightness (Level).
- So the action will be a command to Kitchen Counter 1 with command "SET_CTBR" and parameters: K=3000, D=5000, BR=200.
- The condition checks for COC "DFON" from Kitchen Counter 1.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Set brightness and color temp on physical turn on of Kitchen Counter 1",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Kitchen Counter 1",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "Kitchen Counter 1",
      "command": "SET_CTBR",
      "parameters": [
        { "name": "K", "value": 3000, "uom": "kelvin", "precision": 1 },
        { "name": "D", "value": 5000, "uom": "millisecond", "precision": 1 },
        { "name": "BR", "value": 200, "uom": "level", "precision": 1 }
      ]
    }
  }
}
